cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.GT

This paper deals with optimization of transmission strategies in wireless networks, which is a topic related to network protocols and information theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves optimization techniques and decision-making processes, which are relevant to the categories cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). Finally, the paper discusses the dependence of optimal strategies on network constraints, which is a topic related to game theory and optimization, making cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) a possible category as well.
